The combine harvester consists of cutting unit, threshing unit and cleaning and grain handling units. The cutting section includes reel, cutter bar, an auger and a feeder conveyer. The grain handling section consists of a grain elevator and a discharge auger. The crop after being cut is delivered to the cylinder and concave assembly through feeder conveyor where it is threshed and the grains and straw is separated in different sections. The grain can be directly loaded into the trolley.

Monocrotophos (36 WSC) 10 ml is soaked in absorbent cotton and placed on the affected stem by removing the bark of 2.5 cm. Application of carbofuran 3 G @ 5g per bore hole and plugging with mud after mechanically removing or killing the grub by introducing a needle or wire will also control the pest.
